{"questionId":"19558","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Don took part in a project investigating wind speed,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>km h</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, and the time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> minutes, to fully charge a solar powered robot.</p>\n<p>The investigation was carried out six times. The results are recorded in the table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7fae578ee2d78784d130772c4fd52752e5cc9780.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>M</mtext></math> is the point with coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><menclose notation=\"top\"><mi>x</mi></menclose><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><menclose notation=\"top\"><mi>y</mi></menclose><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math>, Pearson’s product–moment correlation coefficient.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>944</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>943733</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(G2</strong></em><em><strong>)<br><br></strong></em><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(G1)</strong></em>&nbsp;for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>943</mn></math> (incorrect rounding).<br><br><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19558","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.T_1d.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate r, Pearson’s product–moment correlation coefficient.","paper":"2","level":"SL","quest